                    android:text="Before Blood Donation"
                    android:textColor="#FFFFFF"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:textStyle="bold" />

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                    android:paddingLeft="20dp"
                    android:text="1. Ensure that you have slept well for minimum 6 hours.\n\n
2. Eat something in last 4 hours.\n\n
3.As a donor, it is your responsibility to ensure the quality of blood you’re donating.\n
4.You must be above 18 years of age.\n\n
5.You should not be underweight. Usually donors weighing more than 45-50kg are acceptable.\n\n
6.You should not be suffering from any infectious (such as a cold or flu) or chronic diseases (such as diabetes).\n\n
7.You should not have taken any intoxicating drugs, orally or otherwise, within 48 hours prior to donating blood.\n\n
8.You should not have high blood pressure.\n\n
9.You should not be pregnant or menstruating.\n\n
10.Your haemoglobin is 12.5 gm% minimum.\n\n
12.Donate only when Your last blood donation was 3 months earlier.\n\n
13.Must carry any photo with address proof for verification purpose.\n\n
14. Do not smoke 2 hours prior to blood donation.\n\n
15. Do not consume alcohol at least 24 hours prior to blood donation."
                    android:textColor="#000"
                    android:textSize="16dp" />

                <TextView
