                    android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                    android:paddingLeft="20dp"
                    android:text="1. Eat and drink something before leaving.\n\n
2. Have more liquid intakes on the day.\n\n
3. Avoid consuming alcohol for 24 hours after donation.\n\n
4. Don’t smoke or chew gutka for next 2 hours.\n\n
5. If there is bleeding from the punctured site, fold the arm.\n\n
6. If fainting or dizziness occurs, lie down on floor with your legs raised with the stool support.\n\n
7. You can go to work immediately after donating blood, doctors advise avoidance of intense physical exertion.\n\n
8. Resume all normal activities if no symptoms occur.\n\n
9. Remove bandage next day.\n\n
10. If fainting or dizziness occurs for longer time and does not subside, please seek medical help."
                    android:textColor="#000"
                    android:textSize="16dp" />
